{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WmiohtbBebwXnDAsk4CQmB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24\n     2→\n     3→### 10-4-rust-provider — create-story (2026-03-24T09:14Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **Ambiguity in epic definition:** Story notes mention `'library'` AppType for Rust, but `AppType` union in `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` has no `'library'` variant — only `'generic'`. Followed actual code behavior (returns `'generic'`).\n     6→- **Bevy system libs:** Story notes mention Bevy detection for Docker system libs, but no such logic exists in current `dockerfile-template.ts`. Deferred to avoid scope creep.\n     7→- **Risk — workspace aggregation ordering:** No cross-provider ordering concern in the provider pattern; handled within Rust provider alone.\n     8→- **Observation:** All 27 ACs are `cli-verifiable`. No external system dependencies for unit testing.\n     9→\n    10→### 10-4-rust-provider — dev-story (2026-03-24T09:24Z)\n    11→\n    12→No issues reported. 55/55 new tests pass, 3397/3397 total tests pass, no regressions.\n    13→\n    14→### 10-4-rust-provider — code-review (2026-03-24T09:34Z)\n    15→\n    16→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Misleading JSDoc in `hasCargoDep` — example was backwards.\n    17→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Missing false-positive prevention tests for crate substring matching (2 tests added).\n    18→- **LOW (not fixed):** `hasCargoDep` matches commented-out dependencies. Pre-existing behavior from `stack-detect.ts`.\n    19→- **LOW (not fixed):** `getCargoDepsSection` doesn't handle `[dependencies.foo]` subsection format. Pre-existing behavior.\n    20→- **Coverage gap:** No integration test for `installOtlp` success path (requires `cargo` binary).\n    21→\n    22→### 10-5-migrate-consumers-to-stackprovider — create-story (2026-03-24T09:43Z)\n    23→\n    24→- **Risk:** AC17 (`verify-prompt.ts`) compares `AppType` not `StackName` — could false-positive boundary tests.\n    25→- **Risk:** AC16 (`teardown.ts`) accesses state field not local variable — migration needs state shape understanding.\n    26→- **Risk:** `detectAppType()` export chain may break if `stack-detect.ts` deleted before re-export verified.\n    27→- **Observation:** `otlp.ts` is heaviest migration target (~10 stack conditionals). `scanner.ts` had zero stack conditionals.\n    28→\n    29→### 10-5-migrate-consumers-to-stackprovider — dev-story (2026-03-24T09:55Z)\n    30→\n    31→- **Coverage tool name mismatch (tech debt):** `StackProvider.getCoverageTool()` returns `CoverageToolName` values (`'tarpaulin'`, `'coverage-py'`) but `HarnessState.coverage.tool` uses different strings (`'cargo-tarpaulin'`, `'coverage.py'`). Docs-scaffold had to use hardcoded lookup instead of provider delegation.\n    32→- **RustProvider.getBuildCommands() duplication:** Returns `['cargo build', 'cargo test']` from `getBuildCommands()` and `['cargo test']` from `getTestCommands()`, causing `cargo test` to appear twice in generated AGENTS.md. Pre-existing provider design issue.\n    33→- **AGENTS.md format change:** Old hardcoded Rust section had inline comments and `cargo tarpaulin` line. Provider-based output omits these. Minor behavioral change, test updated.\n    34→- **verify-prompt.ts intentional exception:** Uses `projectType === 'nodejs'` (`PromptProjectType`, not `StackName`). Documented in boundary test's `ALLOWED_EXCEPTIONS` per AC17.\n    35→- **teardown.ts uses `.includes('nodejs')`:** String literal reference to stack name outside `src/lib/stacks/`, but acceptable per AC16 (array membership test allowed).\n    36→\n    37→### 10-5-migrate-consumers-to-stackprovider — code-review (2026-03-24T10:03Z)\n    38→\n    39→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Unused import `_detectStack` in `src/lib/stacks/index.ts` — imported but never referenced.\n    40→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Stale comment in `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` — referenced deleted `stack-detect.ts`.\n    41→- **LOW (not fixed):** `coverage.ts` uses local dispatch map instead of delegating to `provider.detectCoverageConfig()` — consumer `CoverageToolInfo` type differs from provider type. Future refactoring opportunity.\n    42→- **LOW (not fixed):** Multiple files use stack name strings as object keys in dispatch maps. Maintenance burden when adding 4th stack.\n    43→- **LOW (not fixed):** `verify/env.ts` `STACK_TO_PROJECT_TYPE` map is redundant given StackName/ProjectType value overlap.\n    44→- **Architecture concern:** `CoverageToolInfo` exists in two incompatible forms (consumer vs provider). Pre-existing, not introduced by this story.\n    45→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6707468c-554d-4568-9ea5-0d04d4a85f59","uuid":"5b6ad906-f10e-48eb-ad47-9ee26b3af40f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T10:13:31.218Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24\n\n### 10-4-rust-provider — create-story (2026-03-24T09:14Z)\n\n- **Ambiguity in epic definition:** Story notes mention `'library'` AppType for Rust, but `AppType` union in `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` has no `'library'` variant — only `'generic'`. Followed actual code behavior (returns `'generic'`).\n- **Bevy system libs:** Story notes mention Bevy detection for Docker system libs, but no such logic exists in current `dockerfile-template.ts`. Deferred to avoid scope creep.\n- **Risk — workspace aggregation ordering:** No cross-provider ordering concern in the provider pattern; handled within Rust provider alone.\n- **Observation:** All 27 ACs are `cli-verifiable`. No external system dependencies for unit testing.\n\n### 10-4-rust-provider — dev-story (2026-03-24T09:24Z)\n\nNo issues reported. 55/55 new tests pass, 3397/3397 total tests pass, no regressions.\n\n### 10-4-rust-provider — code-review (2026-03-24T09:34Z)\n\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Misleading JSDoc in `hasCargoDep` — example was backwards.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Missing false-positive prevention tests for crate substring matching (2 tests added).\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `hasCargoDep` matches commented-out dependencies. Pre-existing behavior from `stack-detect.ts`.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `getCargoDepsSection` doesn't handle `[dependencies.foo]` subsection format. Pre-existing behavior.\n- **Coverage gap:** No integration test for `installOtlp` success path (requires `cargo` binary).\n\n### 10-5-migrate-consumers-to-stackprovider — create-story (2026-03-24T09:43Z)\n\n- **Risk:** AC17 (`verify-prompt.ts`) compares `AppType` not `StackName` — could false-positive boundary tests.\n- **Risk:** AC16 (`teardown.ts`) accesses state field not local variable — migration needs state shape understanding.\n- **Risk:** `detectAppType()` export chain may break if `stack-detect.ts` deleted before re-export verified.\n- **Observation:** `otlp.ts` is heaviest migration target (~10 stack conditionals). `scanner.ts` had zero stack conditionals.\n\n### 10-5-migrate-consumers-to-stackprovider — dev-story (2026-03-24T09:55Z)\n\n- **Coverage tool name mismatch (tech debt):** `StackProvider.getCoverageTool()` returns `CoverageToolName` values (`'tarpaulin'`, `'coverage-py'`) but `HarnessState.coverage.tool` uses different strings (`'cargo-tarpaulin'`, `'coverage.py'`). Docs-scaffold had to use hardcoded lookup instead of provider delegation.\n- **RustProvider.getBuildCommands() duplication:** Returns `['cargo build', 'cargo test']` from `getBuildCommands()` and `['cargo test']` from `getTestCommands()`, causing `cargo test` to appear twice in generated AGENTS.md. Pre-existing provider design issue.\n- **AGENTS.md format change:** Old hardcoded Rust section had inline comments and `cargo tarpaulin` line. Provider-based output omits these. Minor behavioral change, test updated.\n- **verify-prompt.ts intentional exception:** Uses `projectType === 'nodejs'` (`PromptProjectType`, not `StackName`). Documented in boundary test's `ALLOWED_EXCEPTIONS` per AC17.\n- **teardown.ts uses `.includes('nodejs')`:** String literal reference to stack name outside `src/lib/stacks/`, but acceptable per AC16 (array membership test allowed).\n\n### 10-5-migrate-consumers-to-stackprovider — code-review (2026-03-24T10:03Z)\n\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Unused import `_detectStack` in `src/lib/stacks/index.ts` — imported but never referenced.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Stale comment in `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` — referenced deleted `stack-detect.ts`.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `coverage.ts` uses local dispatch map instead of delegating to `provider.detectCoverageConfig()` — consumer `CoverageToolInfo` type differs from provider type. Future refactoring opportunity.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Multiple files use stack name strings as object keys in dispatch maps. Maintenance burden when adding 4th stack.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `verify/env.ts` `STACK_TO_PROJECT_TYPE` map is redundant given StackName/ProjectType value overlap.\n- **Architecture concern:** `CoverageToolInfo` exists in two incompatible forms (consumer vs provider). Pre-existing, not introduced by this story.\n","numLines":45,"startLine":1,"totalLines":45}}}
